1
00:00:17,562 --> 00:00:20,522
DON'T LOOK NOW

2
00:01:16,850 --> 00:01:19,810
Action Man patrol, open fire!

3
00:01:22,931 --> 00:01:25,891
This is your Commander speaking.

4
00:01:31,612 --> 00:01:34,052
Mortar attack, dig in!

5
00:02:34,021 --> 00:02:36,261
What are you reading?

6
00:02:36,701 --> 00:02:40,981
I'm trying to answer Christine's
question: If the world is round,

7
00:02:41,422 --> 00:02:43,582
why is a frozen pond flat?

8
00:02:50,943 --> 00:02:52,903
That's a good question.

9
00:03:21,588 --> 00:03:24,428
"Lake Ontario
curves more than 3 degrees from its

10
00:03:24,868 --> 00:03:28,348
east to its west shore".
Frozen water isn't flat!

11
00:03:28,789 --> 00:03:32,069
Nothing is what it seems.
- My cigarettes...

12
00:03:32,509 --> 00:03:34,509
Did you put the slides together?

13
00:03:35,110 --> 00:03:37,830
No, I put the duplicates in my tray.

14
00:03:53,112 --> 00:03:56,072
Action Man patrol, fall in.

15
00:03:57,233 --> 00:04:00,393
Enemy in sight. Range one thousand.

16
00:04:09,514 --> 00:04:10,954
Oh shit!

17
00:04:40,359 --> 00:04:42,319
What's the matter?

18
00:04:43,439 --> 00:04:44,639
Nothing.

19
00:04:55,321 --> 00:04:56,681
Dad!

20
00:07:14,180 --> 00:07:16,220
Everything is rotten.

21
00:07:16,661 --> 00:07:18,781
The stone is like tobacco.

22
00:07:19,221 --> 00:07:21,181
Should I carry on?

23
00:07:22,181 --> 00:07:26,061
No. It's already late.
Let's call it a day.

24
00:07:26,502 --> 00:07:29,222
My wife's waiting for me.

25
00:07:29,662 --> 00:07:33,942
See you tomorrow at San Nicol?
- Yeah, exactly.

26
00:07:34,383 --> 00:07:36,343
Thanks a lot!

27
00:07:46,625 --> 00:07:47,825
Ciao!

28
00:08:12,588 --> 00:08:14,548
Hi!
- Hi.

29
00:08:15,629 --> 00:08:18,189
What are you doing?
- Writing to Johnny. - What?

30
00:08:18,629 --> 00:08:20,589
Just a letter. How'd it go?

31
00:08:21,030 --> 00:08:26,030
The deeper we go, the more Byzantine.
I'm restoring a fake.

32
00:08:26,470 --> 00:08:29,510
And you can't change course?
- They haven't enough bread.

33
00:08:29,951 --> 00:08:34,031
The options are restore the fake
or let it sink in the sea.

34
00:08:34,472 --> 00:08:39,952
What did you say?
- I said, "Daddy's still hard at work

35
00:08:40,392 --> 00:08:43,792
on the windows of St. Nicholas,
our 16th century church.

36
00:08:44,233 --> 00:08:47,193
His repairs
are no different than the originals.

37
00:08:47,633 --> 00:08:51,113
I'll send you slides,
maybe you can tell. Hope Ellies

38
00:08:51,554 --> 00:08:55,954
is more reasonable this term.
I think that's his Captain.

39
00:08:56,395 --> 00:09:00,995
"I'm enclosing the money
for your gym shoes. Buy the ones

40
00:09:01,435 --> 00:09:04,995
with the padded soles."
Another boring letter.

41
00:09:05,436 --> 00:09:07,916
God, it's cold.

42
00:09:14,237 --> 00:09:15,997
I've got something in my eye.

43
00:09:24,519 --> 00:09:28,879
Do you want me to add something?
- Why not send him a card yourself?

44
00:09:29,319 --> 00:09:34,199
It's so cold in here and
the waiters won't come. Hello!

45
00:09:43,241 --> 00:09:45,441
I must take some time off.

46
00:09:46,962 --> 00:09:48,162
Signori?

47
00:09:48,882 --> 00:09:52,962
What do you want?
- I'll have what I had last night.

48
00:09:53,403 --> 00:09:57,203
Pollo sopresso, scampi al ferri,

49
00:09:57,643 --> 00:10:02,803
vino bianco, due insalate verdi...
Good, that's it.

50
00:10:03,244 --> 00:10:05,404
Did you see the bishop today?
- No.

51
00:10:05,844 --> 00:10:08,724
I'm terribly sorry!

52
00:10:09,165 --> 00:10:10,365
Sorry.

53
00:10:12,885 --> 00:10:16,845
What?
- No, she's got something in her eye.

54
00:10:21,647 --> 00:10:24,887
I think I'd better go help them.

55
00:10:25,487 --> 00:10:29,407
Perhaps I can show you where it is.
- Oh, it's awfully kind of you.

56
00:10:52,371 --> 00:10:54,771
I hope you don't think us rude.

57
00:10:55,211 --> 00:10:56,251
Rude? Why?

58
00:10:56,691 --> 00:10:58,611
Staring at you out there.

59
00:10:59,052 --> 00:11:02,692
Comes from the country.
Country people always stare more.

60
00:11:03,132 --> 00:11:07,012
I'm frightfully sorry.
- I didn't notice it even if you were.

61
00:11:07,453 --> 00:11:09,493
Which eye is it?
- The left one.

62
00:11:09,933 --> 00:11:12,773
Well, let me help.
- Help! - I can try.

63
00:11:13,214 --> 00:11:15,414
No!
You nearly put Jocelyn's eye out

64
00:11:15,854 --> 00:11:18,174
the last time you tried poking about.

65
00:11:20,895 --> 00:11:22,055
Perhaps...

66
00:11:22,495 --> 00:11:25,175
...perhaps I can help?

67
00:11:25,615 --> 00:11:27,615
That's awfully kind.

68
00:11:28,056 --> 00:11:29,256
Oh dear.

69
00:11:31,376 --> 00:11:34,216
My sister is blind you see.

70
00:11:35,697 --> 00:11:37,897
I see.
- Yes.

71
00:12:17,983 --> 00:12:20,383
That's it. It was a tiny

72
00:12:20,823 --> 00:12:25,423
black speck. I think I've got it.
- Well done.

73
00:12:25,864 --> 00:12:28,064
Thank you very much. Goodness.

74
00:12:28,504 --> 00:12:30,384
You do remind me of my daughter.

75
00:12:30,825 --> 00:12:35,265
Really?
- Only her hair is darker.

76
00:12:36,265 --> 00:12:37,985
Your handkerchief.

77
00:12:40,146 --> 00:12:44,386
You're sad...
and there's no need to be!

78
00:12:45,747 --> 00:12:48,827
My sister's psychic.
- She wants you to know...

79
00:12:49,267 --> 00:12:53,587
I've seen her and she
wants you to know that she's happy.

80
00:12:54,028 --> 00:12:58,308
I've seen your little girl
sitting between you and your husband

81
00:12:58,949 --> 00:13:01,029
and she was laughing!

82
00:13:01,469 --> 00:13:02,549
Yes,

83
00:13:02,989 --> 00:13:05,789
she was with you!

84
00:13:06,230 --> 00:13:07,990
And she's laughing!

85
00:13:08,430 --> 00:13:11,390
I'm sorry if we stared.

86
00:13:15,591 --> 00:13:19,311
She's wearing a shiny little mac.

87
00:13:20,592 --> 00:13:22,192
Christine!

88
00:13:22,632 --> 00:13:24,592
But she's laughing!

89
00:13:25,032 --> 00:13:26,992
She's happy as can be!

90
00:13:40,594 --> 00:13:45,074
You're very like her.
The forehead, the eyes...

91
00:13:48,595 --> 00:13:50,555
Is that better?
- Yes.

92
00:13:50,996 --> 00:13:54,036
Shall I fetch your husband?
- No. I'm alright, thank you.

93
00:13:54,476 --> 00:13:56,036
Jolly good!

94
00:13:56,477 --> 00:13:58,797
Just leave me alone. I'll be fine.

95
00:13:59,237 --> 00:14:01,197
Alright, my dear.

96
00:14:05,478 --> 00:14:08,358
Did you

97
00:14:08,798 --> 00:14:10,678
really see her?

98
00:14:12,039 --> 00:14:14,759
She was there.

99
00:14:15,199 --> 00:14:17,159
She was there!

100
00:14:30,641 --> 00:14:34,481
I thought you were right.
I felt you should.

101
00:14:41,603 --> 00:14:43,083
Signore.

102
00:15:01,926 --> 00:15:04,326
I sent your food back to be warmed.

103
00:15:04,766 --> 00:15:09,766
The mastic that works it is number 3.
- Oh dear, John, I must stand up.

104
00:15:46,332 --> 00:15:49,172
Hey!
- I'm sorry.

105
00:15:52,493 --> 00:15:54,453
Signore!
- Thanks.

106
00:16:00,014 --> 00:16:02,134
That's it then.

107
00:16:47,140 --> 00:16:50,580
They're only children here!
- It was the nearest hospital.

108
00:16:51,021 --> 00:16:53,981
I was playing with them.
- The doctor... - John?

109
00:16:54,422 --> 00:16:58,382
Christine is still with us.
- Christine's dead, Laura.

110
00:16:58,822 --> 00:17:01,982
Christine's dead.
- I know, of course!

111
00:17:02,423 --> 00:17:04,703
The two ladies in the restaurant,

112
00:17:05,143 --> 00:17:07,663
they were watching us while we ate.

113
00:17:08,103 --> 00:17:12,583
They told me they could see
Christine sitting between us.

114
00:17:13,024 --> 00:17:17,224
This is two people we don't even know!
Listen! Listen now!

115
00:17:17,665 --> 00:17:21,065
There's one that's blind,
she has the second sight.

116
00:17:21,505 --> 00:17:25,265
She described to me
Christine's red plastic mac.

117
00:17:26,306 --> 00:17:30,066
Laura...
- John, I'm perfectly alright!

118
00:17:30,507 --> 00:17:34,587
I haven't felt as good as this
in months and months!

119
00:17:35,027 --> 00:17:39,987
I don't need pills,
I'm not going crazy. I feel great!

120
00:17:41,508 --> 00:17:46,788
When did the doctor say you could go?
- Anytime. I only fainted.

121
00:17:47,869 --> 00:17:51,229
I wish you'd believe me.
I really feel fine.

122
00:17:51,670 --> 00:17:54,670
I really feel good at last!
- I believe you!

123
00:17:55,110 --> 00:17:57,510
Seeing is believing.

124
00:17:59,751 --> 00:18:02,191
Put your shoes on.

125
00:18:16,393 --> 00:18:20,273
Out of the way!
- Stop! Stay there!

126
00:18:20,714 --> 00:18:22,794
But I must go through!

127
00:18:23,234 --> 00:18:25,474
A homicide occurred here!

128
00:18:25,914 --> 00:18:29,994
What's going on?
- A homicide. You must stop.

129
00:18:32,595 --> 00:18:36,315
What did he say? Homicide?
- Yeah.

130
00:18:39,036 --> 00:18:41,836
Stop!
- But I must go through!

131
00:18:43,037 --> 00:18:45,997
You can't. Stop now!

132
00:18:49,038 --> 00:18:51,758
What are you doing?

133
00:18:53,638 --> 00:18:56,038
Turn left!

134
00:18:56,479 --> 00:18:58,519
You can't go through here.

135
00:19:04,760 --> 00:19:08,800
Isn't this where you were with...
- No.

136
00:19:16,041 --> 00:19:18,001
I want to stop at this church.

137
00:19:19,042 --> 00:19:22,682
It's closed. Why that one?

138
00:19:24,443 --> 00:19:28,323
I just wanted to...
I want to say a prayer.

139
00:19:29,163 --> 00:19:31,683
Oh, Laura!

140
00:19:43,685 --> 00:19:47,165
I don't like this church at all.
- But I do.

141
00:19:54,327 --> 00:19:56,767
Do you have any change?
- Yes.

142
00:19:57,967 --> 00:20:01,367
I'm going to light a candle for her.
- How much are candles?

143
00:20:01,808 --> 00:20:03,128
Fifty.

144
00:20:03,568 --> 00:20:06,288
I don't have any fifties.

145
00:20:06,728 --> 00:20:09,688
Maybe I'll light six.

146
00:20:19,130 --> 00:20:21,730
Thank you, my love.

147
00:21:01,056 --> 00:21:02,896
The Madonna by Antonio Rizzo

148
00:21:03,336 --> 00:21:07,856
in about 1 490.
The grille work is also by Rizzo.

149
00:21:08,297 --> 00:21:10,257
Note the flowers woven into...

150
00:21:33,141 --> 00:21:35,701
Jesus!
- You hypocrite!

151
00:21:36,141 --> 00:21:38,341
The bishop!
I'm an hour and a half late!

152
00:21:38,781 --> 00:21:41,181
In the name of the Father, the Son,

153
00:21:41,622 --> 00:21:46,382
and the Holy Spirit. Amen.
May the mercy and

154
00:21:46,822 --> 00:21:49,782
Iove of our Father
and the peace of the Holy Spirit

155
00:21:50,223 --> 00:21:52,183
be with you.

156
00:22:11,106 --> 00:22:12,826
How are you, John?

157
00:22:13,746 --> 00:22:15,786
It was entirely my fault.

158
00:22:16,227 --> 00:22:19,267
It wasn't John's fault.
- A woman to share your sins with.

159
00:22:19,907 --> 00:22:21,747
Laura, you're looking better.

160
00:22:22,587 --> 00:22:26,307
I'm really terribly sorry.
- It's okay.

161
00:22:26,828 --> 00:22:30,548
These workmen took me around.
We have made some great advances.

162
00:22:30,989 --> 00:22:34,829
I'd like you to look at the mosaics
that need to be refired.

163
00:22:35,269 --> 00:22:40,229
I've already been much too long.
When are you coming to stay with me?

164
00:22:40,670 --> 00:22:44,430
Thursday, if that's alright?
- I look forward to it.

165
00:22:46,271 --> 00:22:50,671
I took some samples from the pilings.
We're in trouble down there, too.

166
00:22:51,111 --> 00:22:55,831
The churches belong to God, but
he doesn't seem to care about them.

167
00:22:59,073 --> 00:23:01,833
Does he have other priorities?

168
00:23:03,513 --> 00:23:06,153
We have stopped listening.

169
00:23:07,554 --> 00:23:10,514
Are you a Christian, Laura?

170
00:23:11,554 --> 00:23:15,634
I don't know.
I'm kind to animals and children.

171
00:23:16,395 --> 00:23:17,555
St. Nicholas

172
00:23:17,995 --> 00:23:22,955
of this church is the Patron Saint
of scholars and children. Interesting.

173
00:23:26,196 --> 00:23:28,236
We must talk, John!

174
00:23:28,677 --> 00:23:32,157
Thursday I'll have your room ready.
- Thank you.

175
00:23:32,597 --> 00:23:36,717
I'll have the mastic samples by then.
Acidity is ruining all the adhesives.

176
00:23:37,158 --> 00:23:40,438
I look forward to hearing about it.
Thursday.

177
00:23:40,878 --> 00:23:43,798
Ciao.
- Goodbye!

178
00:23:45,959 --> 00:23:49,159
He doesn't give an
ecclesiastical fuck about the church.

179
00:23:49,600 --> 00:23:54,000
Why did he ask me if I was Christian?
- Because you kissed his ring.

180
00:23:54,440 --> 00:23:57,400
What in God's name made you do that?

181
00:23:58,801 --> 00:24:02,001
Ciao Giorgio!
- See you tomorrow! - Yes.

182
00:24:06,602 --> 00:24:11,322
You know? Your bishop really
makes me feel quite uneasy.

183
00:24:11,763 --> 00:24:14,883
He probably makes God
feel less than immaculate.

184
00:24:15,323 --> 00:24:17,043
Signor!
- No.

185
00:24:17,484 --> 00:24:21,684
The key!
- I have the key.

186
00:24:22,124 --> 00:24:24,724
He has the key!

187
00:24:25,165 --> 00:24:28,005
Be careful! If you ruin it,

188
00:24:28,605 --> 00:24:30,685
I don't know what I'd do!

189
00:24:37,686 --> 00:24:40,406
I'm going
to get down to some work tomorrow.

190
00:24:40,847 --> 00:24:43,447
Enough of this idling around.

191
00:24:44,847 --> 00:24:46,367
What?

192
00:24:51,448 --> 00:24:56,408
Don't we have to book at this place?
I don't want what happened last time!

193
00:24:57,649 --> 00:25:00,089
What place?
- John!

194
00:25:00,530 --> 00:25:02,890
The place we're going to be eating at!

195
00:25:03,330 --> 00:25:05,890
Yeah, sure.

196
00:25:07,050 --> 00:25:10,010
Where is my Neutralgina then?

197
00:25:17,772 --> 00:25:20,212
You'll have to read this!

198
00:25:30,134 --> 00:25:32,334
What are you doing?

199
00:25:33,014 --> 00:25:35,734
I can't hear what you're saying.
- I'm shouting!

200
00:25:36,175 --> 00:25:38,815
I still can't hear.
- What are you doing?

201
00:25:39,255 --> 00:25:41,455
I'm having a bath.

202
00:25:41,895 --> 00:25:44,695
You heard me that time.

203
00:26:24,381 --> 00:26:28,621
You know those lumps are coming back
on the side of your waist?

204
00:26:30,702 --> 00:26:32,622
See?

205
00:26:44,944 --> 00:26:47,904
85 kilos, which is 1 90 pounds.

206
00:26:52,625 --> 00:26:55,585
You okay?
- I'm okay.

207
00:27:21,669 --> 00:27:22,869
Come in!

208
00:27:23,470 --> 00:27:26,030
May I tidy up?
- Yes, yes.

209
00:27:30,071 --> 00:27:32,591
I'll come back later.

210
00:27:42,712 --> 00:27:45,832
It's a miracle
I didn't hurt myself when I fainted.

211
00:27:46,273 --> 00:27:50,153
The unconscious body reacts faster
than the mind ever can.

212
00:27:51,353 --> 00:27:53,313
Perhaps.

213
00:27:54,714 --> 00:27:56,714
You have toothpaste on your mouth.

214
00:28:02,075 --> 00:28:04,555
Eat it off!

215
00:28:09,196 --> 00:28:11,916
I can't get it off.

216
00:28:19,477 --> 00:28:21,157
This.

217
00:32:37,314 --> 00:32:39,514
Yes.
- No.

218
00:32:39,954 --> 00:32:41,914
Really?
- Yes.

219
00:32:44,555 --> 00:32:47,715
You will be eating here tonight,
I hope?

220
00:32:48,155 --> 00:32:50,675
No, we're eating out tonight.

221
00:32:51,115 --> 00:32:53,475
Too bad. Have a good night.

222
00:32:53,916 --> 00:32:57,356
Thank you.
- Good night.

223
00:32:59,917 --> 00:33:02,877
You can to go home.

224
00:33:21,520 --> 00:33:26,480
Come here, I think I found the way!
- We went over this bridge already!

225
00:33:28,401 --> 00:33:31,121
I never minded being lost in Venice.

226
00:33:33,521 --> 00:33:36,841
Now, we take the second left
and then the first left or right.

227
00:33:37,282 --> 00:33:39,242
Oh, yeah?
- Yeah.

228
00:33:41,242 --> 00:33:44,202
A nice dark little alley!

229
00:33:46,723 --> 00:33:49,283
Yes, this is it.
- It isn't.

230
00:33:49,724 --> 00:33:52,044
Yes, it is.
- It isn't, John.

231
00:33:52,484 --> 00:33:56,444
Come on.
- No, it isn't.

232
00:34:12,007 --> 00:34:15,367
Oh, rats! I'm getting out of here.

233
00:34:18,888 --> 00:34:21,488
I know this place.

234
00:34:32,610 --> 00:34:34,650
This is it! It's Ponte Giretto!

235
00:34:35,450 --> 00:34:36,930
What?
- Here!

236
00:34:38,010 --> 00:34:39,450
- No, I...

237
00:34:53,133 --> 00:34:57,213
What's that, John?
- It's okay, I found the real world.

238
00:34:57,653 --> 00:34:59,093
Come on.

239
00:35:06,334 --> 00:35:09,734
What on earth was that?
- A cat or a rat.

240
00:35:10,215 --> 00:35:13,175
Maybe something else.
- A rat?

241
00:35:21,657 --> 00:35:24,897
This was just around the corner
from where we were!

242
00:35:25,337 --> 00:35:28,297
I know where we are now.

243
00:35:34,978 --> 00:35:37,498
Ready?
- Slow!

244
00:35:51,541 --> 00:35:53,021
Slow!

245
00:35:54,901 --> 00:35:57,221
Yeah. Higher.

246
00:35:58,222 --> 00:36:00,662
Beautiful. Good.

247
00:36:21,585 --> 00:36:23,465
Ready?
- No!

248
00:36:23,905 --> 00:36:26,425
It'll fall down!

249
00:36:29,706 --> 00:36:30,666
Go!

250
00:36:31,626 --> 00:36:32,666
Go!

251
00:36:35,867 --> 00:36:37,627
Are you ready?

252
00:36:49,949 --> 00:36:51,149
Hello!

253
00:36:51,869 --> 00:36:53,669
Hello!
- Hello!

254
00:36:54,109 --> 00:36:56,949
How extraordinary to see you.
Oh, it's Mrs. Baxter.

255
