01:05:37,951 --> 01:05:39,151
Thank you.

513
01:06:30,958 --> 01:06:32,158
Laura!

514
01:06:40,160 --> 01:06:41,600
Laura!

515
01:06:55,602 --> 01:06:57,762
Hey, watch out!

516
01:07:26,886 --> 01:07:31,366
Where is the manager?
- It is closed, Signore.

517
01:07:48,929 --> 01:07:51,449
Signor Alexander...
- Signor Baxter...

518
01:07:51,890 --> 01:07:57,050
I thought... the end of the season,
you understand. It's my holiday.

519
01:07:57,490 --> 01:08:00,810
Has Mrs. Baxter come back here?
- La Signora?

520
01:08:01,251 --> 01:08:05,571
My wife, yes. Has she come back here?
- But she left this morning.

521
01:08:06,012 --> 01:08:09,092
I just saw her on the Grand Canal.

522
01:08:09,532 --> 01:08:13,492
Has she come back here?
- She missed the plane?

523
01:08:13,933 --> 01:08:16,773
No, I'm just asking
if my wife's come back here!

524
01:08:17,213 --> 01:08:21,173
No, Signore.
We are closed.

525
01:08:27,215 --> 01:08:28,695
Momi!

526
01:08:29,135 --> 01:08:32,175
Haven't you hung up the sign yet?

527
01:08:32,615 --> 01:08:36,175
We hang up the sign,
and they come anyway!

528
01:08:49,818 --> 01:08:54,778
My luggage get away all right? - Yes.
- You didn't see my wife? - No.

529
01:10:23,231 --> 01:10:24,431
Yes.

530
01:10:25,071 --> 01:10:26,271
Here.

531
01:10:28,231 --> 01:10:29,231
Yes.

532
01:10:29,672 --> 01:10:32,112
He's ready.

533
01:10:37,873 --> 01:10:40,593
The inspector is in room 87.

534
01:10:41,033 --> 01:10:43,833
Room 87.
- Yes. I hope that helps.

535
01:10:44,274 --> 01:10:46,714
Thank you.
- Goodbye.

536
01:11:17,278 --> 01:11:18,238
Hello!

537
01:11:21,399 --> 01:11:24,359
Sit down, Mr. Baxter.

538
01:11:25,119 --> 01:11:29,519
This is your wife,
and these are the sketches.

539
01:11:29,960 --> 01:11:34,920
How are they?
- I guess you'd recognize them.

540
01:11:37,641 --> 01:11:42,801
Age makes women grow to look more
like each other. Don't you find that?

541
01:11:44,722 --> 01:11:48,682
Old men decay
and each becomes quite distinct.

542
01:11:49,683 --> 01:11:52,763
Women seem to converge, eh?

543
01:11:53,963 --> 01:11:59,243
I hadn't thought about it.
- The skill of the police artist

544
01:12:00,204 --> 01:12:03,244
is to make the living appear dead.

545
01:12:08,525 --> 01:12:11,485
You no longer stay at the "Europa"?

546
01:12:13,366 --> 01:12:15,326
No, it closed for the winter.

547
01:12:16,527 --> 01:12:20,127
Tell me
what happened from the beginning.

548
01:12:20,567 --> 01:12:23,407
My wife met these two women...

549
01:12:23,848 --> 01:12:26,288
a couple of days ago.

550
01:12:26,728 --> 01:12:31,848
The blind one claimed to have seen
Christine, our dead daughter.

551
01:12:32,889 --> 01:12:35,769
She said Christine was happy.

552
01:12:36,209 --> 01:12:40,249
My wife collapsed.
When she came round she was changed.

553
01:12:40,690 --> 01:12:44,450
She was happy,
she had come to terms with the death.

554
01:12:45,691 --> 01:12:48,691
She... she was...

555
01:12:49,131 --> 01:12:51,771
her whole self again. We...
- Did you have a row?

556
01:12:52,212 --> 01:12:55,412
A row? No, well...

557
01:12:57,092 --> 01:12:59,972
I was only trying to protect her.

558
01:13:00,413 --> 01:13:04,973
It didn't make any difference
because she saw the women anyway.

559
01:13:05,413 --> 01:13:08,333
And when she came back,

560
01:13:08,774 --> 01:13:11,654
last night, we went to bed.

561
01:13:12,094 --> 01:13:14,654
There was a call from England.

562
01:13:15,095 --> 01:13:20,735
Our son goes to school in England.
They told us he had an accident.

563
01:13:21,176 --> 01:13:24,216
My wife said that she had been warned.

564
01:13:24,576 --> 01:13:27,016
She got on the first plane to England.

565
01:13:27,457 --> 01:13:32,897
I saw her go. I put her on the boat.
I saw her leave at 8:30.

566
01:13:34,378 --> 01:13:36,898
Have you called the airport?

567
01:13:37,338 --> 01:13:41,698
Yes. The plane was full,
that's all I know.

568
01:13:44,339 --> 01:13:48,819
Please go on.
- Then I saw her.

569
01:13:49,540 --> 01:13:54,180
Between 1 0:30 and 1 1:00 on a boat.
I was on a Vaporetto.

570
01:13:54,620 --> 01:13:57,900
She's here in Venice
with those two women.

571
01:14:00,381 --> 01:14:03,501
What is it, Mr. Baxter?

572
01:14:04,542 --> 01:14:06,582
I do not understand.

573
01:14:07,182 --> 01:14:12,142
If she's in Venice,
surely she will get in touch with you.

574
01:14:13,583 --> 01:14:15,903
If she can.

575
01:14:17,384 --> 01:14:19,904
What is it you fear?

576
01:14:28,145 --> 01:14:31,105
A killer
on the loose, the murderer...

577
01:14:33,986 --> 01:14:36,946
My wife is not a well woman.

578
01:14:39,027 --> 01:14:40,227
Yes.

579
01:14:41,787 --> 01:14:43,747
Yes, of course.

580
01:14:46,188 --> 01:14:49,148
I would have thought...

581
01:14:52,828 --> 01:14:58,388
there must be more.
- No, no. There is nothing more.

582
01:14:59,029 --> 01:15:03,149
My wife got something
from these two women,

583
01:15:03,590 --> 01:15:08,670
something that neither doctors nor I
could give her, something she needed,

584
01:15:09,111 --> 01:15:11,631
so she went with them.
Where?

585
01:15:12,071 --> 01:15:14,831
Where I don't know. I was

586
01:15:15,272 --> 01:15:19,552
in the pensione last night,
where they lived. Today l,

587
01:15:19,992 --> 01:15:24,232
before I came here, I looked for it.
It's vanished.

588
01:15:29,314 --> 01:15:31,274
So now she's with them.

589
01:15:39,875 --> 01:15:43,955
Why should one criticize you
for being worried?

590
01:15:44,396 --> 01:15:47,356
Thank you for talking to me.

591
01:15:47,956 --> 01:15:50,996
I am grateful.
- Okay, I'll be at the

592
01:15:51,477 --> 01:15:53,357
Palazzo Vendori.

593
01:15:54,237 --> 01:15:57,717
I want you to help me. Try again.

594
01:15:58,158 --> 01:16:00,558
Try to find the pensione.

595
01:16:00,998 --> 01:16:05,958
It will make me feel that we have
your cooperation in a real way.

596
01:16:09,039 --> 01:16:13,359
I don't even know where to start.

597
01:16:13,800 --> 01:16:17,240
Start from where
you saw them the last time.

598
01:16:18,721 --> 01:16:19,681
Okay.

599
01:16:20,121 --> 01:16:22,161
Good luck.
- Thank you.

600
01:16:22,601 --> 01:16:24,041
Where did you say?

601
01:16:24,481 --> 01:16:26,401
San Nicol?dei Mendicoli.

602
01:16:26,842 --> 01:16:28,562
Ah, yes.

603
01:16:37,763 --> 01:16:39,323
Pronto? Sabbione?

604
01:16:39,763 --> 01:16:43,883
Follow Signor Baxter
from San Nicola church.

605
01:20:33,516 --> 01:20:34,716
Hello!

606
01:20:35,516 --> 01:20:38,476
Is anyone here? Hello!

607
01:20:40,437 --> 01:20:44,677
Ah, hello Signora.
Do you speak English? - No.

608
01:20:45,118 --> 01:20:48,838
Two old ladies... Sisters...

609
01:20:49,278 --> 01:20:52,238
One...
- Nina!

610
01:20:54,559 --> 01:20:58,439
Hello, Signora. Two...
Do you speak English? - No.

611
01:20:58,880 --> 01:21:02,600
Two old ladies...

612
01:21:03,040 --> 01:21:05,640
Sisters. One...

613
01:21:06,081 --> 01:21:10,641
What's that called? So. Yes?

614
01:21:11,081 --> 01:21:13,921
Ah! Come along.
- Scottish women.

615
01:21:14,362 --> 01:21:17,322
They left this morning.
- A woman was with them.

616
01:21:17,762 --> 01:21:19,602
Yes. My wife.

617
01:21:20,043 --> 01:21:22,003
Come along.

618
01:21:31,044 --> 01:21:33,204
But where are they?
- Gone.

619
01:21:34,245 --> 01:21:38,245
But where? - They left today.
Do you want this room?

620
01:21:38,685 --> 01:21:41,125
Me? No, thank you.

621
01:21:53,407 --> 01:21:55,567
Where?
- I don't know. You?

622
01:21:56,008 --> 01:21:57,168
No.

623
01:21:57,608 --> 01:22:00,368
Excuse me. Thank you, Mr. Baxter.

624
01:22:00,808 --> 01:22:03,368
Who are you?
- Sabbione,

625
01:22:03,809 --> 01:22:06,049
Homicide.

626
01:22:09,930 --> 01:22:13,130
They're not here.

627
01:22:23,292 --> 01:22:26,252
Yes. Very nice!

628
01:22:30,933 --> 01:22:33,893
Yes, Signor?
- I'm expected. - Your name?

629
01:22:34,333 --> 01:22:39,413
Baxter. John Baxter.
- Mr. Baxter! He's seeing people now.

630
01:22:39,854 --> 01:22:43,814
I'll tell him that you are here.
- Thank you.

631
01:22:57,296 --> 01:23:00,256
Your Excellency,
Signor Baxter is here.

632
01:23:07,898 --> 01:23:11,858
Do we have the medical results?
- Yes, Excellency.

633
01:23:22,660 --> 01:23:26,940
Sister... - He won't be long.
- I've to make a call to England.

634
01:23:27,381 --> 01:23:32,341
It's urgent. Could I use that phone?
- You'll have to complete this form.

635
01:23:38,422 --> 01:23:41,782
Can I dial that here?
- Yes.

636
01:23:47,903 --> 01:23:50,663
Pronto! To England, please.

637
01:24:01,105 --> 01:24:03,065
Mrs. Babbage? John Baxter.

638
01:24:03,506 --> 01:24:05,346
Hello!
- Hello.

639
01:24:05,786 --> 01:24:08,026
I've been trying to ring you,

640
01:24:08,466 --> 01:24:10,946
but the wire's down or something.

641
01:24:11,387 --> 01:24:14,227
Johnny's absolutely fine!

642
01:24:14,667 --> 01:24:19,027
Quite right as rain. He woke up
this morning with no headache.

643
01:24:19,468 --> 01:24:21,468
Fit as a fiddle! The doctor's

644
01:24:21,908 --> 01:24:26,588
let him get up,
and he's now playing around.

645
01:24:27,029 --> 01:24:29,229
And it wasn't a concussion.

646
01:24:29,669 --> 01:24:32,949
Johnny can remember everthing.
- That's marvelous.

647
01:24:33,390 --> 01:24:36,790
It's something they have to watch.
- Yes.

648
01:24:37,230 --> 01:24:40,390
I suppose you'd like to speak
to your wife... - Sorry?

649
01:24:40,831 --> 01:24:41,951
Here she is.

650
01:24:43,071 --> 01:24:45,471
I...
- Hello, darling. What?

651
01:24:45,912 --> 01:24:48,632
Laura?
- Johnny's perfectly alright.

652
01:24:49,072 --> 01:24:51,432
There's nothing wrong,

653
01:24:51,872 --> 01:24:55,672
absolutely nothing. He just has
this little bumb on his forehead.

654
01:24:56,113 --> 01:24:58,233
Are you alright? Where are you?

655
01:24:58,673 --> 01:25:03,993
I'm at Alberto's.
- I'm catching the 9 o'clock plane.

656
01:25:04,434 --> 01:25:08,994
I don't know what time it gets in,
but we can have a late dinner.

657
01:25:09,435 --> 01:25:11,555
Everything is very good.

658
01:25:11,995 --> 01:25:15,035
John's fine, and I'm okay.

659
01:25:15,476 --> 01:25:18,716
I thought I saw you here.
I thought I saw you

660
01:25:19,156 --> 01:25:22,796
with the two sisters.
I was certain, I swear it!

661
01:25:23,237 --> 01:25:26,197
Alright, don't worry, sweetheart!

662
01:25:26,637 --> 01:25:30,637
I found the flight number.
- Laura, where are you?

663
01:25:31,078 --> 01:25:34,798
I'm at Porton, John!
Johnny and I just had tea.

664
01:25:35,238 --> 01:25:40,198
It's arriving at 1 1:00.
- Just a second, I'll get a pencil.

665
01:25:40,799 --> 01:25:45,639
I'll come straight to Alberto's.
- Okay, I'll wait...

666
01:25:46,080 --> 01:25:50,040
I'll see you about eleven, okay?
- Yes. - John, alright?

667
01:25:50,481 --> 01:25:53,441
Okay.
- John, Alright? - Yes.

668
01:25:53,881 --> 01:25:57,841
I love you. Bye.
- Okay, bye.

669
01:26:01,082 --> 01:26:03,882
Let Jesus Christ

670
01:26:04,322 --> 01:26:09,602
lead your heart and spirit
down the right path.

671
01:26:10,043 --> 01:26:11,003
Amen.

672
01:26:15,244 --> 01:26:17,884
John! Are you feeling alright?

673
01:26:18,324 --> 01:26:21,964
Yes. Excuse me, Alberto.

674
01:26:22,405 --> 01:26:25,365
I think I just have to...

675
01:26:26,366 --> 01:26:29,086
May I use your telephone?
- Sure.

676
01:26:40,408 --> 01:26:44,848
I don't blame you moving in here.
I would have done the same myself.

677
01:26:45,288 --> 01:26:50,408
Do you want to see Johnny again?
- No, thank you. I've said goodbye.

678
01:26:50,849 --> 01:26:54,809
Mrs. Baxter, I think
it would probably be quicker.

679
01:27:05,731 --> 01:27:08,371
Good evening.
- Where are the English women?

680
01:27:08,812 --> 01:27:11,252
Up the stairs.

681
01:27:20,853 --> 01:27:22,053
Wendy?

682
01:27:23,094 --> 01:27:24,294
Answer me!

683
01:27:26,654 --> 01:27:30,054
It's me, John Baxter.
Laura's husband.

684
01:27:30,495 --> 01:27:33,295
What's happened to Wendy?
Where is she?

685
01:27:33,735 --> 01:27:35,895
I don't know, I'll find out.

686
01:27:36,335 --> 01:27:39,455
I don't know what's happening.
- Yes, I know.

687
01:27:40,296 --> 01:27:43,456
Where is the other?
- At the British Consulate.

688
01:27:43,896 --> 01:27:46,016
She was very furious.

689
01:27:47,297 --> 01:27:52,257
She's at the British Consulate.
- Yes, but that was hours ago!

690
01:27:53,458 --> 01:27:57,098
It's half past nine now.
I don't know this room.

691
01:27:57,538 --> 01:28:00,058
I want to go home to the hotel.

692
01:28:01,899 --> 01:28:05,179
This is a Police Station.
I don't want to stay here.

693
01:28:05,619 --> 01:28:09,659
I can't tell you how sorry I am.
There was a misunderstanding...

694
01:28:10,100 --> 01:28:13,900
They took us out of our hotel.
We were arrested.

695
01:28:14,341 --> 01:28:19,141
Then they asked us about your wife...
- I know. I'm truly sorry.

696
01:28:19,581 --> 01:28:22,261
I'm taking you back now.
- Yes, please.

697
01:28:22,702 --> 01:28:24,422
May she?
- Yes.

698
01:28:24,862 --> 01:28:28,822
If I could just take your arm?
- Sure.

699
01:28:32,623 --> 01:28:37,263
You can't understand the noises
in a place like this.

700
01:28:37,864 --> 01:28:41,584
I'm so sorry. I just feel that...

701
01:28:42,025 --> 01:28:45,225
If you could just take me back.

702
01:29:12,909 --> 01:29:14,869
Signora Baxter?
- Yes.

703
01:29:15,309 --> 01:29:18,869
More luggage?
- No. You send by Barberigo? - Yes.

704
01:29:19,310 --> 01:29:22,750
Okay. Do you speak English?
- A little.

705
01:29:24,391 --> 01:29:27,991
In Venice I love that
it's so safe for me to walk.

706
01:29:28,431 --> 01:29:31,391
Watch, steps.
- Thank you.

707
01:29:32,752 --> 01:29:36,672
The sound changes, you see,
as you come to a canal,

708
01:29:37,112 --> 01:29:41,072
and the echoes from the walls
are so clear.

709
01:29:41,793 --> 01:29:45,753
My sister hates it.
- That's too bad.

710
01:29:46,994 --> 01:29:50,714
She says it's like a city in aspic,

711
01:29:51,154 --> 01:29:55,874
left over from a dinner party,
and all the guests are dead and gone.

712
01:29:56,915 --> 01:30:00,875
It frightens her. Too many shadows.

713
01:30:03,916 --> 01:30:06,876
We are almost there.
- Yes.

714
01:30:08,877 --> 01:30:12,677
Milton loved this city.
Did you know that?

715
01:30:13,117 --> 01:30:15,077
No. It's interesting.

716
01:30:23,199 --> 01:30:26,039
This isn't the right way, is it?

717
01:30:26,479 --> 01:30:30,079
The Palazzo di Conte Barberigo.
- Yes, yes.

718
01:30:30,520 --> 01:30:35,000
This is the wrong way!
- I'm taking you to Signor Baxter.

719
01:30:35,440 --> 01:30:38,360
Yes?
- He is at the Police Station.

720
01:30:38,801 --> 01:30:41,241
It is just along the way.

721
01:30:53,203 --> 01:30:56,763
I've tried to keep them.
They never stay.

722
01:30:57,204 --> 01:30:59,684
They're very wild in Venice.

723
01:31:01,204 --> 01:31:04,164
Do you like cats, Mr. Baxter?
- Yes.

724
01:31:04,925 --> 01:31:09,605
I like them alright,
but they don't like me very much.

725
01:31:10,045 --> 01:31:12,485
Here's the hotel.
- Thank you.

726
01:31:12,926 --> 01:31:15,046
These are swinging doors.
- I remember.

727
01:31:15,486 --> 01:31:19,766
I'll keep them open.
- It's so reassuring to have a man.

728
01:31:20,207 --> 01:31:24,567
We changed hotels cause Wendy said
there were prowlers. And it was dirty.

729
01:31:26,648 --> 01:31:29,608
Careful of the steps.
- Thank you.

730
01:31:30,408 --> 01:31:33,088
Here is the key.
- Thank you.

731
01:31:33,529 --> 01:31:35,969
Room 307.
- 307, good.

732
01:31:38,489 --> 01:31:40,929
Okay, it's here.

733
01:31:47,211 --> 01:31:52,691
They said you left at the station.
- Mr. Baxter's been looking after me.

734
01:31:53,051 --> 01:31:56,171
Has he?
- Yes, she was at the Police Station,

735
01:31:56,612 --> 01:31:59,572
and had been there quite a while
and I thought...

736
01:32:00,732 --> 01:32:04,092
They found your wife then?
- Yes... the killings...

737
01:32:04,533 --> 01:32:09,493
He's explained everything. Have we a
drop of Whisky for him? You'll stay?

738
01:32:09,934 --> 01:32:12,934
Yes.
- There's the miniatures.

739
01:32:13,614 --> 01:32:16,214
We're leaving tomorrow.

740
01:32:16,655 --> 01:32:19,735
Have you put the photographs out?
- Yes.

741
01:32:20,175 --> 01:32:22,655
Just a glass of water for me.

742
01:32:23,096 --> 01:32:27,056
I'll fetch it.
Do take a seat, Mr. Baxter.

743
01:32:41,138 --> 01:32:45,218
So you can find it quite easily.

744
01:32:45,659 --> 01:32:46,859
Thank you.

745
01:32:49,299 --> 01:32:50,259
Thank you.

746
01:32:51,379 --> 01:32:54,099
Doesn't really look like her.
- It doesn't matter.

747
01:32:54,540 --> 01:32:56,980
No?
- No.

748
01:32:59,461 --> 01:33:02,501
Please, your photograph.

749
01:33:03,421 --> 01:33:04,381
What?

750
01:33:07,982 --> 01:33:09,222
My God!

751
01:33:10,462 --> 01:33:14,422
Thank you for your help. Bye-bye.

752
01:33:14,863 --> 01:33:16,823
Goodbye.

753
01:33:34,506 --> 01:33:35,466
Thank you.

754
01:33:35,906 --> 01:33:38,866
You're wearing odd socks.
- You put out my clothes.

755
01:33:39,306 --> 01:33:41,506
I know. I was merely informing you.
- Thank you.

756
01:33:42,347 --> 01:33:46,587
I must go... - You've been wearing
them all day. - Let him be off.

757
01:33:47,027 --> 01:33:51,347
Wait! - Is there anything I can do?
- No, it's alright. Goodbye.

